{"identifier": "cs_email10:2ba2f511", "prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
You are a support ticket routing assistant. Analyze the following ticket and route it to the appropriate team member, returning a dictionary with a single key 'route_to' and the team member's name in lowercase as the value.

PRIMARY SUPPORT AREAS:
• Ankush (Data): Data migrations, imports/exports, database syncs, encoding issues
• Tom (Platform): Browser compatibility, login systems, password resets, website technical issues
• Jerry (Mobile): Mobile app functionality, notifications, app updates, mobile-specific issues
• Ben (Billing): Individual payment processing, subscription changes, refunds, invoicing

SPECIALIZED SUPPORT AREAS:
• Nuno (Security): Data protection, GDPR compliance, privacy policies, security audits
• Will (Product): UI/UX design, reporting features, dashboards, feature requests
• Sarah (Integration): API support, technical connectivity, SDK issues, webhook setup
• Miles (Admin): Team management, permissions, user roles, organizational setup
• Julia (Education): Training resources, documentation, webinars, learning materials
• Harrison (Enterprise): Support plans, volume licensing, enterprise solutions, custom deployments

ROUTING RULES:
1. Mobile app issues ALWAYS go to Jerry, even if they involve other areas
2. Website/browser issues go to Tom unless specifically about visual design
3. Enterprise-scale requests go to Harrison, even if billing-related
4. Training/documentation requests always route to Julia
5. For technical integration issues, prefer Sarah over Will
6. Security compliance questions always go to Nuno
